close_reason: "Implemented compact mutation output by default with explicit full/id-only compatibility controls, 87.82% packed output reduction, MCP parity, token budgets, docs, and tests."
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/437\n\n## Problem\nEvery CLI mutation echoes the full updated item + full `changed_fields` by default (368 B for a trivial create vs 29 B `--id-only` — 12.7x). MCP is already compact by default (`changed_field_count`, `idOnly`/`fullChangedFields` opt-ins), so the CLI is the more verbose surface and inconsistent with MCP.\n\n## Proposed fix\nMake CLI mutation default lean: `{ id, status, changed_field_count }` (+ `close_reason` on close). Full echo behind `--full` / `--full-changed-fields`; existing `--id-only`/`--quiet` stay. Config knob (e.g. `output_lean_mutations`) so the default is project-tunable; respect back-compat for scripts via config.\n\n## Definition of done\nLean default (or config-flipped default) with parity spec vs MCP compact output; docs/AGENTS.md updated; contracts:update run; measured token reduction recorded on this item."
